# Vivado docker image
This Dockerfile allows to generate a vivado docker image.

Vivado is a very big tool (around 70GB when installed) to build the docker image you need around 200GB available space on your hard disk drive.

## Download Vivado install file 
The installer can be downloaded here :

https://www.xilinx.com/member/forms/download/xef.html?filename=Xilinx_Unified_2020.1_0602_1208.tar.gz

## Generate Vivado install_config.txt
This file is given in the repository but if you want to change installation parameters you can run the commands below.

	tar xzf Xilinx_Unified_2020.1_0602_1208.tar.gz
	Xilinx_Unified_2020.1_0602_1208/xsetup -b ConfigGen

## Building docker image
First the vivado install file shall be copied into docker/vivado directory:

	cp Xilinx_Unified_2020.1_0602_1208.tar.gz docker/vivado
	cd docker/vivado

And build the command below to build the image :

	docker build -t vivado-2020.1:0.2 .

When image is built, it is viewable in docker images list:

	root@dockerHugo:~/docker/vivado# docker images 
	REPOSITORY          TAG                 IMAGE ID            CREATED             SIZE
	vivado-2020.1       0.2                 cfcbdfca5c68        17 hours ago        73.8GB


